      "content": "i'm writing a paper for my constitutional law class and i'm stuck on a debate. some people say the current supreme court is just being originalist to follow what the founders meant with the 2nd amendment, but others call it judicial activism. from a scholarly perspective, is one of those ways of looking at it actually more legally sound than the other?",
